      <div class="section-num">07</div>
      <div class="section-title">Music + Performance — Joy of Being</div>
    </div>
    <p class="lead">Not separate from the research. IS the research. F dimension (Fun/Creative) in ABCDEFG in embodied action.</p>

    <div class="music-grid">
      <div class="music-card">
        <span class="music-icon">🎵</span>
        <div class="music-title">Blueprint EP</div>
        <div class="music-text">Makēda's own project. Personal IP. Separate from Quest Labs. The creative practice that grounds the practitioner-researcher. The art that proves the epistemology.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="music-card">
        <span class="music-icon">🎭</span>
        <div class="music-title">Baksana Dance Company</div>
        <div class="music-text">Makēda's avatar = live action role playing. The embodied dimension of futures practice. The Shero's Journey made physical. Playing futures in the body before naming them in words.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="music-card">
        <span class="music-icon">☀️</span>
        <div class="music-title">Joy of Being</div>
        <div class="music-text" style="font-style:normal">"I hang out with my friends over the summer, do cool music and dance and get paid for it. It helps me stay connected to my body during the winter." — This IS the methodology. This is also funded through the Quest Card Joy of Being column.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="callout callout-red">
      <div class="callout-label">Why this is academically defensible</div>
      The F (Fun/Creative) dimension of ABCDEFG argues that joy produces the psychological safety required for genuine futures thinking. Milojević's feminist eutopia requires it. Dunagan's experiential futures assume it. Sardar's call for creativity as the response to postnormal times demands it. Blueprint, Baksana, viola, and summer music with friends are not indulgences. They are field notes.
    </div>
